  "text": [
    "Across North Wales",
    "The snowflakes wander,",
    "A swarm of white bees.",
    "Over the woods",
    "A cold veil lies.",
    "A load of chalk",
    "Bows down the trees.",
    "No undergrowth",
    "Without its wool,",
    "No field unsheeted;",
    "No path is left",
    "Through any field;",
    "On every stump",
    "White flour is milled.",
    "Will someone tell me",
    "What angels lift",
    "Planks in the flour-loft",
    "Floor of heaven",
    "Shaking down dust?",
    "An angel\u2019s cloak",
    "Is cold quicksilver.",
    "And here below",
    "The big drifts blow,",
    "Blow and billow",
    "Across the heather",
    "Like swollen bellies.",
    "The frozen foam",
    "Falls in fleeces.",
    "Out of my house",
    "I will not stir",
    "For any girl",
    "To have my coat",
    "Look like a miller\u2019s",
    "Or stuck with feathers",
    "Of eider down.",
    "What a great fall",
    "Lies on my country!",
    "A wide wall, stretching",
    "One sea to the other,",
    "Greater and graver",
    "Than the sea\u2019s graveyard.",
    "When will rain come?"
  ],
  "title": "The Winter",
